<br>
My problem is shadow knights.  I've met at least three non-RPing SKs.  Fair enough, they don't RP, doesn't bother me.  I've grouped with two of them.  That may sound strange, but bear in mind that I joined during downtime, and I have grouped with one of them twice (now refered to as X.)<br>
<br>
The first SK wasn't so bad, I didn't know he was an SK until he started fighting.  You don't tend to, mainly because non-RPing SKs simply see pallys as not the scum of Norrath (like I like it) but as cut down clerics.  I got invited because a friend of mine was in the group.  So, I'm in this group, and suddenly, RP sirens start going off.  I'm grouped with an SK, entirely by accident.  So, what do I do?  Do I abandon my friend (who was also duped) or just group and fight.  I stayed, and got a fair amount of exp.  My &quot;Ding&quot;-esque message, which was entirely IC was completely ignored, greeted with &quot;wot/?&quot;  I eventually got sick of it and left.  Fair enough, friend followed me.  We excused ourselves and left.<br>
<br>
Sooo...  Second incident, involving Mr. X.  I've grouped with X twice now, and I don't care to again.  The first time was in Paludal Caverns.  Another situation where you don't realize they are an SK until they start fighting.  My friend had to leave, and so I'm stuck in this group with an SK.  I'm trying my absolute bloody hardest to stay IC here.  Fair enough, eventually he gets bored and buggers off.  I leave shortly after.<br>
<br>
Second time, I'm with that friend again.  We're just about to join a group with a barbarian warrior and his little wood elf ranger friend.  My friend leaves shortly before joining, and a chanter (good aligned) wanders along and joins.  GREAT!  We're having a wail of a time, we're pretty IC and enjoying it.  Here comes Mr. X.  The ranger, who was neutral and the warrior who was neutral had no problem with it.  The chanter and I are grinding in our boots right now.  So, Mr X joins in.  He's a fair bit more powerful than I am, so he gets the haste instead, much to the chargrin of the chanter (obviously, if it were not for IC concerns, there wouldn't be a problem).  This time, I leave, hopefully getting away from this SK for the last time.<br>
<br>
He tracks me down.  Despite the fact that the chanter and I were making our selection to never group with SKs VERY CLEAR other than in circumstances outside of our control, SK wanders over, hails, get's a minimal response.<br>
<br>
Then comes the inevitable question:<br>
<br>
&quot;Want to group?&quot;<br>
<br>
I politely send him a /tell explaining my IC reasons for never grouping with SKs.  I'm apparently being childish and stubborn by holding this view.  He's a powerful ally, according to him, and I'm being ridiculous for not grouping with him.<br>
<br>
This is a roleplaying server.  A paladin is a holy knight, a shadowknight is an unholy knight.  Where does he get off claiming I'm being childish for refusing to group with a fricking SK for RP reasons?  I don't give a crap how useful he is, OOC I have no problem with the player, but IC, my character sees everything that is wrong with the world in that damned SK.  Why can people not understand that?  Why must I be made to feel like a pillock for passing up obvious grouping opportunities for RP reasons?  Why can people not respect the fact that I play this game as I see fit, and if it involves me, and if it involves a decision I have made about my character, they have NO RIGHT to tell me that I'm being childish, especially on the only server to actually cater for these needs.<br>
<br>
Mr X, for being abusive, annoying, and downright pissing me off, you've earned first place on my /ignore list.  Amazing, something I never thought I would ever have to use.  Kudos, you've broken a record. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=castinareleas>CastinarEleas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 111<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/14/02 10:15:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=644.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Just amazed I even have to use here...</span><hr size=1> /comfort<br>
